{
  "stem": "7157.2",
  "chunk_idx": 1,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 7.7,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And it was, it was obvious to, I guess, everyone.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "I mean, even-- I remember seeing people on the street, dead.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "I remember Germans shooting people in the ghetto, just when they felt like it.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "It was very dangerous to be a child, at that point, too.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "Because believe it or not, the Germans would you know, be able to pick up children and just kill them brutally, to put it very bluntly.",
      "word_count": 26
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "So, just one incident that kind of stands out very much in the ghetto was the Germans would go search apartments.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And many cases, when they searched apartments, they were looking for people that are not working, you know, that maybe are hiding and not going out to work.",
      "word_count": 28
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "So I remember my grandmother knew-- saw them coming, knew they were coming.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "She put us in a cupboard, closed the door to this cupboard, of course told my brother and I to be very, very quiet.",
      "word_count": 24
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And somehow-- you know, it just amazes me, even today.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "You know, I was seven years old, but when I was told to be quiet, I guess the fear was so strong that I was quiet.",
      "word_count": 26
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "And this was kind of throughout the war.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "I always wondered, as my own children were growing up and I couldn't keep them quiet, I said, how is it possible that I was able to do this?",
      "word_count": 29
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "But I guess it was the fear.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Anyway, she put us in this cupboard.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And she was smart enough-- and this was the second time my grandmother saved my life.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "She was smart enough to place wood in front of the door of this cupboard.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "She piled up a whole bunch of wood, in front of this cupboard.",
      "word_count": 13
    }
  ],
